From: Antonio Radici <antonio@debian.org>
Date: Thu, 27 Feb 2014 16:06:15 +0100
Subject: use_usr_bin_editor

Even if EDITOR is not set, mutt will always use /usr/bin/editor
(which is set by update-alternatives), rather than falling back
to vi.
---
 init.c | 2 +-
 init.h | 2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

Index: neomutt/init.c
===================================================================
--- neomutt.orig/init.c
+++ neomutt/init.c
@@ -3972,7 +3972,7 @@ void mutt_init(int skip_sys_rc, struct L
   {
     p = mutt_str_getenv("EDITOR");
     if (!p)
-      p = "vi";
+      p = "/usr/bin/editor";
   }
   Editor = mutt_str_strdup(p);
   Visual = mutt_str_strdup(p);
Index: neomutt/init.h
===================================================================
